1
00:00:31,364 --> 00:00:33,324
THIS DRAMA IS FICTION
AND THE ELEMENTS OF THE STORY

2
00:00:33,408 --> 00:00:34,492
HAVE NO RELATION TO REALITY

3
00:00:38,329 --> 00:00:40,832
All right. Attention.

4
00:00:40,915 --> 00:00:43,418
Stop what you're doing and gather around.

5
00:00:43,835 --> 00:00:44,878
Hurry!

6
00:00:48,256 --> 00:00:49,382
Director Kwon.

7
00:00:55,180 --> 00:00:56,389
Everyone.

8
00:00:56,723 --> 00:01:01,895
A colleague who occupied that room
in the corner over there

9
00:01:02,937 --> 00:01:04,314
has left our company.

10
00:01:07,650 --> 00:01:10,236
But Mr. Baek didn't lose face.

11
00:01:12,655 --> 00:01:16,409
The process of recruiting Mr. Gil,
who tarnished our club's reputation,

12
00:01:17,243 --> 00:01:20,872
and using his position to facilitate
corruption in recruitment

13
00:01:21,372 --> 00:01:24,042
provide enough grounds for his dismissal.

14
00:01:24,125 --> 00:01:25,877
Later. Go protest later.

15
00:01:25,960 --> 00:01:27,462
There was no corruption involved.

16
00:01:27,545 --> 00:01:29,631
Why is he bringing up
Gil Chang-ju's recruitment now?

17
00:01:29,714 --> 00:01:32,258
Are you going to fight the owner's nephew
in front of everyone?

18
00:01:32,342 --> 00:01:34,928
But this is all wrong.

19
00:01:35,011 --> 00:01:37,013
Is justification more important?

20
00:01:37,305 --> 00:01:39,933
The process is more important
at the company.

21
00:01:40,016 --> 00:01:42,811
But we worried about Mr. Baek's future.

22
00:01:43,103 --> 00:01:45,230
We allowed him to resign voluntarily

23
00:01:45,313 --> 00:01:49,192
and will give him his pay
until he finds another job.

24
00:01:50,151 --> 00:01:51,611
He's quite a character.

25
00:01:52,028 --> 00:01:53,655
Why is he saying that here?

26
00:01:53,988 --> 00:01:55,865
Before we find a new general manager,

27
00:01:55,949 --> 00:01:58,201
I'm sure your workload
will be more demanding,

28
00:01:58,284 --> 00:02:00,912
but I ask of you to continue working hard.

29
00:02:03,748 --> 00:02:06,668
We can fill in
the empty space of one person.

30
00:02:08,962 --> 00:02:10,672
Where is the general manager?

31
00:02:10,755 --> 00:02:13,383
I wouldn't know.

32
00:02:17,762 --> 00:02:20,723
It's unjust to hold him responsible

33
00:02:20,890 --> 00:02:22,475
for Mr. Gil at this point.

34
00:02:22,559 --> 00:02:26,396
And also, the recruitment process
of Baek Young-soo was fair.

35
00:02:26,479 --> 00:02:27,897
Even Yoo Kyung-taek

36
00:02:28,148 --> 00:02:29,732
knew him beforehand.

37
00:02:29,816 --> 00:02:33,570
-They did know him, but--
-I understand, Ms. Lee.

38
00:02:34,654 --> 00:02:37,157
Worry about getting the team
back on track.

39
00:02:38,783 --> 00:02:41,286
I don't exactly know
what you say you're understanding.

40
00:02:43,163 --> 00:02:45,999
I understand what you're feeling
about Mr. Baek.

41
00:02:47,083 --> 00:02:50,503
So get out and worry about getting
the team back to normal.

42
00:02:51,379 --> 00:02:54,507
Ms. Lee, you're
the temporary general manager.

43
00:02:55,592 --> 00:02:56,718
Why me?

44
00:03:01,347 --> 00:03:04,058
If I leave without being
able to understand what's going on,

45
00:03:04,142 --> 00:03:05,977
I can't serve as interim general manager

46
00:03:06,060 --> 00:03:08,313
or worry about getting
the team back on track.

47
00:03:09,355 --> 00:03:12,108
Mr. Baek agreed to this compromise,

48
00:03:12,192 --> 00:03:14,861
and we are allowing
his brother to work here.

49
00:03:14,944 --> 00:03:16,738
If you start to act like this,

50
00:03:16,821 --> 00:03:20,200
who do you think will see
the most damage if you do this?

51
00:03:21,826 --> 00:03:24,996
What are you going to do
if his brother gets fired as well?

52
00:03:29,918 --> 00:03:32,212
PRESIDENT'S OFFICE

53
00:03:34,214 --> 00:03:35,548
MR. BAEK

54
00:03:41,221 --> 00:03:43,973
Your call could not be connected and...

55
00:03:52,941 --> 00:03:54,108
Hello?

56
00:03:56,569 --> 00:03:57,528
What?

57
00:03:58,988 --> 00:04:01,157
No, it's not determined.

58
00:04:01,574 --> 00:04:02,951
I'm going to handle it.

59
00:04:05,286 --> 00:04:07,580
How did you know about what's
going on in our club?

60
00:04:10,124 --> 00:04:10,959
What?

61
00:04:13,586 --> 00:04:15,588
-Sir.
-Why?

62
00:04:16,881 --> 00:04:18,841
Don't you have any companionship
for a colleague?

63
00:04:21,052 --> 00:04:22,595
What kind of power do I have?

64
00:04:22,679 --> 00:04:25,223
How does an article regarding
his voluntary resignation come out

65
00:04:25,306 --> 00:04:26,975
ten minutes after he left?

66
00:04:30,687 --> 00:04:34,774
-Unless you prepared it in advance.
-That's what we do with the athletes.

67
00:04:34,857 --> 00:04:36,985
That's what we do with the athletes.

68
00:04:37,068 --> 00:04:39,195
Why can't we do that
with the general manager?

69
00:04:40,947 --> 00:04:44,117
We can also be fired like this.

70
00:04:44,367 --> 00:04:47,745
If I didn't spread the news,
it could have happened to me.

71
00:04:50,748 --> 00:04:51,708
Yes.

72
00:04:53,668 --> 00:04:54,752
So you did it...

73
00:04:56,254 --> 00:04:57,755
because they told you to.

74
00:05:17,608 --> 00:05:19,485
I'm going back to tell him.

75
00:05:20,445 --> 00:05:23,448
Firing the general manager
like this is unjust.

76
00:05:25,700 --> 00:05:26,951
The rest of you...

77
00:05:29,912 --> 00:05:31,748
are going to stay still, right?

78
00:05:35,501 --> 00:05:37,837
I know the general manager isn't kind.

79
00:05:38,921 --> 00:05:41,632
But when it came to his attitude
and skills,

80
00:05:41,716 --> 00:05:43,676
is there anyone here who was disappointed?

81
00:05:44,052 --> 00:05:45,219
Or...

82
00:05:47,013 --> 00:05:49,140
does anyone think this is just?

83
00:05:59,817 --> 00:06:01,611
GENERAL MANAGER BAEK SEUNG-SOO

84
00:06:10,661 --> 00:06:11,746
I'm busy.

85
00:06:14,916 --> 00:06:18,628
You were here.
Why haven't you answered my calls?

86
00:06:19,087 --> 00:06:20,213
Because I was busy.

87
00:06:20,713 --> 00:06:23,007
Do you know what has happened?

88
00:06:28,471 --> 00:06:30,848
You knew, but why are you here?

89
00:06:31,265 --> 00:06:33,184
I'm trying to let go of what's on my mind.

90
00:06:35,269 --> 00:06:37,730
Are you going to accept all of this?

91
00:06:37,814 --> 00:06:40,483
You can leave or stay here quietly.

92
00:06:41,442 --> 00:06:42,527
What do you want to do?

93
00:07:06,134 --> 00:07:08,803
In this flash drive, I've put some data

94
00:07:08,886 --> 00:07:11,597
because I thought
I'd be working here for a long time.

95
00:07:11,681 --> 00:07:13,891
Please deliver it
to the new general manager.

96
00:07:14,976 --> 00:07:17,979
Are you just going to quit like this?

97
00:07:29,740 --> 00:07:31,200
To be honest,

98
00:07:32,285 --> 00:07:35,455
seeing the Dreams get last place
without any awareness

99
00:07:35,538 --> 00:07:38,124
of the severity, I once thought
of the team as fat pigs.

100
00:07:40,001 --> 00:07:41,794
But I don't think they go that far.

101
00:07:42,962 --> 00:07:44,005
At times,

102
00:07:45,256 --> 00:07:46,424
they work hard,

103
00:07:47,300 --> 00:07:50,678
compared to what I expected
looking at them always getting last place.

104
00:07:50,761 --> 00:07:51,679
Also, at times...

105
00:07:53,890 --> 00:07:57,852
they showed that they were
willing to sweat and work hard.

106
00:08:00,229 --> 00:08:01,689
And it was good to see.

107
00:08:04,275 --> 00:08:06,319
And please be the interim general manager.

108
00:08:07,737 --> 00:08:08,696
I don't want to.

109
00:08:09,363 --> 00:08:12,408
You aren't my superior anymore.
Why should I listen to your order?

110
00:08:12,783 --> 00:08:14,869
-You'll just be an interim one.
-Still.

111
00:08:14,952 --> 00:08:18,581
If Director Kwon Kyung-min gives an order,
am I not allowed to even say no?

112
00:08:18,664 --> 00:08:23,294
The only thing that I agreed on
with Director Kwon as I left was this.

113
00:08:25,046 --> 00:08:26,964
It's Director Kwon's order.

114
00:08:28,174 --> 00:08:30,384
It's also my last authority.

115
00:08:39,185 --> 00:08:41,729
I have no feelings and attachment
to the Dreams.

116
00:08:41,812 --> 00:08:44,232
I just worked hard because it was my job.

117
00:08:44,857 --> 00:08:45,983
Now that I see it,

118
00:08:46,400 --> 00:08:50,029
I think I should've done this
from the start.

119
00:09:34,740 --> 00:09:37,118
He has done nothing wrong.
Why is he being relegated?

120
00:09:37,201 --> 00:09:38,828
To a Korean wrestling team at that?

121
00:09:38,911 --> 00:09:41,998
They thought that he messed up
after his brother got injured.

122
00:09:42,081 --> 00:09:44,166
He doesn't even have
any relation to sports.

123
00:09:44,250 --> 00:09:45,251
Exactly.

124
00:09:45,334 --> 00:09:47,753
I heard the Korean wrestling team
is breaking up soon.

125
00:10:08,024 --> 00:10:10,067
You have other measures planned, right?

126
00:10:12,153 --> 00:10:13,904
You have other plans, right?

127
00:10:14,822 --> 00:10:17,241
I'm sure you'll return
and surprise everyone. Right?

128
00:10:17,908 --> 00:10:20,911
I have no reason to do that.
I'll get my pay even without working.

129
00:10:20,995 --> 00:10:22,830
You're not working just because of money.

130
00:10:23,956 --> 00:10:25,082
I work because of money.

131
00:10:25,166 --> 00:10:28,544
A person who works only for money
wouldn't work this hard.

132
00:10:29,295 --> 00:10:31,547
Why did you give us hope
in the first place then?

133
00:10:35,760 --> 00:10:39,472
There are people who do everything
to the extreme.

134
00:10:40,973 --> 00:10:44,894
And I don't think I'll get a good result
just by working hard.

135
00:10:47,897 --> 00:10:49,398
It never happened.

136
00:10:49,523 --> 00:10:52,568
There have been good results.
You've been winning all this time.

137
00:10:58,866 --> 00:11:00,785
Thank you for seeing me out.

138
00:11:17,259 --> 00:11:20,012
The way the general manager handled things
was a bit rough.

139
00:11:20,721 --> 00:11:21,597
What's rough about it?

140
00:11:21,681 --> 00:11:24,642
He should know how to conform
to things in life.

141
00:11:25,309 --> 00:11:27,520
He can't talk that way
in front of the director.

142
00:11:29,855 --> 00:11:32,817
But does he work all right?

143
00:11:34,110 --> 00:11:35,027
Yes, he's good.

144
00:11:35,111 --> 00:11:38,322
If he's good, he should be
working in another franchise.

145
00:11:38,739 --> 00:11:42,451
-We knew about it when we hired him.
-Yes. Even so,

146
00:11:42,535 --> 00:11:44,870
when things turned out to be like this,

147
00:11:45,496 --> 00:11:47,998
shouldn't they have
decided to quit together?

148
00:11:49,500 --> 00:11:51,252
Let's get back. We should get to work.

149
00:11:51,335 --> 00:11:54,171
I mean, what's the reason he's still here
when he knows

150
00:11:54,505 --> 00:11:57,466
-how we feel about this?
-I said, let's get back!

151
00:11:57,550 --> 00:11:58,592
Let me get to work.

152
00:12:00,886 --> 00:12:01,762
You...

153
00:12:03,389 --> 00:12:05,975
We're here to discuss the Rule 5 draft.

154
00:12:06,308 --> 00:12:07,977
As you all know,

155
00:12:08,936 --> 00:12:10,020
Mr. Baek has quit.

156
00:12:10,396 --> 00:12:13,858
Poor guy. Why did he have
to deal with it that way?

157
00:12:13,941 --> 00:12:15,317
He started all of this.

158
00:12:15,943 --> 00:12:16,902
What do we do now?

159
00:12:17,570 --> 00:12:18,571
My gosh.

160
00:12:19,697 --> 00:12:22,283
I'll be in charge of the matter
temporarily.

161
00:12:22,366 --> 00:12:25,453
I brought the coaches to hear
about the players.

162
00:12:25,995 --> 00:12:28,664
You should decide
on the 40-man roster first.

163
00:12:28,998 --> 00:12:31,709
Here's the list of our players I've made.

164
00:12:32,126 --> 00:12:35,546
Why isn't Yoo Sung-gu on the list?
He's been first string for years.

165
00:12:35,629 --> 00:12:38,674
He took an active part
as a mop-up player last year.

166
00:12:38,758 --> 00:12:40,176
His ERA has been similar every year,

167
00:12:40,259 --> 00:12:42,261
whereas his left on base percentage
increased.

168
00:12:42,344 --> 00:12:44,889
Among the candidates
to make it to the list,

169
00:12:45,181 --> 00:12:47,516
the strategy analysis team recommends
these players.

170
00:12:47,641 --> 00:12:49,435
This is a bit strange.

171
00:12:49,518 --> 00:12:50,686
Hey, Kyung-taek.

172
00:12:51,312 --> 00:12:53,564
Are you trying to show
that you're working?

173
00:12:53,647 --> 00:12:55,733
This goes against common sense
in the field.

174
00:12:55,816 --> 00:12:58,527
No, it goes against the opinions
of the coaching staff.

175
00:12:58,611 --> 00:13:02,364
And please refrain from speaking
so casually if you're not the manager.

176
00:13:02,448 --> 00:13:04,617
You don't get to do that
just because you're my superior.

177
00:13:06,494 --> 00:13:07,661
But you...

178
00:13:08,537 --> 00:13:09,413
Who are you?

179
00:13:09,497 --> 00:13:11,499
He's in charge of data
in the strategy analysis team.

180
00:13:11,749 --> 00:13:13,334
Oh, the general manager's brother?

181
00:13:14,627 --> 00:13:16,420
His name is Baek Young-soo.

182
00:13:16,504 --> 00:13:18,214
He's worked
for a baseball column website...

183
00:13:18,297 --> 00:13:19,548
That's all right.

184
00:13:19,632 --> 00:13:21,008
I'm sick of hearing that.

185
00:13:22,092 --> 00:13:24,470
Then he should keep writing columns.

186
00:13:25,137 --> 00:13:27,848
Are we supposed to listen to
his orders then?

187
00:13:31,227 --> 00:13:33,145
This is a mess.

188
00:13:33,312 --> 00:13:34,188
Excuse me.

189
00:13:34,271 --> 00:13:37,107
I don't think even Mr. Baek
would have done this.

190
00:13:37,316 --> 00:13:40,277
I like that you're trying new things...

191
00:13:41,737 --> 00:13:43,030
but I'm not sure about this.

192
00:13:43,906 --> 00:13:45,950
Good meeting, everyone.

193
00:13:59,880 --> 00:14:02,341
You must be taken aback
by what happened suddenly.

194
00:14:04,635 --> 00:14:06,011
My brother called me.

195
00:14:06,846 --> 00:14:08,681
He said he'd kill me if I quit.

196
00:14:08,973 --> 00:14:11,517
Does he say those things to his brother?

197
00:14:11,600 --> 00:14:15,521
In situations like these, I feel
like he still doesn't know me yet.

198
00:14:15,604 --> 00:14:16,981
Why would I quit?

199
00:14:19,859 --> 00:14:22,027
If we were to both walk out of here,

200
00:14:22,111 --> 00:14:23,279
we'd look like trash.

201
00:14:24,780 --> 00:14:28,576
A guy who hired his younger brother
and quit after he got caught,

202
00:14:29,201 --> 00:14:32,288
and another guy who coveted
someone else's position.

203
00:14:32,705 --> 00:14:34,540
PRESIDENT'S OFFICE

204
00:14:37,084 --> 00:14:38,335
ROBERT GIL

205
00:14:40,629 --> 00:14:42,047
The president left work.

206
00:14:42,798 --> 00:14:44,466
-When?
-Just a moment ago.

207
00:15:09,116 --> 00:15:09,950
Mr. Gil?

208
00:15:10,951 --> 00:15:12,745
-Yes?
-It is you.

209
00:15:12,828 --> 00:15:14,496
The one who was naturalized.

210
00:15:14,580 --> 00:15:16,832
-Who are you?
-I'm the acting owner of the club.

211
00:15:17,583 --> 00:15:20,127
-Are you the one that fired Mr. Baek?
-Yes.

212
00:15:21,003 --> 00:15:21,879
Please retract it.

213
00:15:22,254 --> 00:15:24,131
Oh, my.
With what authority do you say that?

214
00:15:24,465 --> 00:15:25,716
It was all my fault.

215
00:15:26,425 --> 00:15:28,552
I was careless during the interview and...

216
00:15:29,803 --> 00:15:30,888
And?

217
00:15:32,097 --> 00:15:33,724
I've lived a wrongful life.

218
00:15:34,642 --> 00:15:36,310
I've lived a wrongful life...

219
00:15:39,063 --> 00:15:40,522
and Mr. Baek is paying for it.

220
00:15:42,024 --> 00:15:45,819
It seems like you're indebted to Mr. Baek.

221
00:15:46,403 --> 00:15:48,072
Let me suggest a better way.

222
00:15:50,074 --> 00:15:52,034
When the season begins,

223
00:15:53,243 --> 00:15:54,787
play baseball really well.

224
00:15:55,788 --> 00:15:56,914
That's how you repay it.

225
00:15:57,373 --> 00:15:58,248
Then...

226
00:15:59,416 --> 00:16:00,709
will you bring back Mr. Baek?

227
00:16:01,627 --> 00:16:02,753
No.

228
00:16:04,588 --> 00:16:05,965
In the future,

229
00:16:06,548 --> 00:16:09,510
you can look back and think, "He was...

230
00:16:10,970 --> 00:16:13,013
a pretty good general manager."

231
00:16:13,722 --> 00:16:15,182
Wouldn't that be enough?

232
00:16:16,266 --> 00:16:17,351
Let's go.

233
00:16:45,087 --> 00:16:46,296
In this flash drive,

234
00:16:46,380 --> 00:16:50,634
I've put some data, because I thought
I'd be working here for a long time.

235
00:16:51,260 --> 00:16:53,137
Please deliver it
to the new general manager.

236
